```cpp
// è¯­è¨€åˆ†ææœåŠ¡å®¢æˆ·ç«¯
class LanguageAnalysisClient {
private:
    std::string serviceEndpoint_;
    HttpClient httpClient_;
    
public:
    struct AnalysisRequest {
        std::string language;
        std::string filePath;
        std::string fileContent;
        nlohmann::json config;
    };
    
    Result<AnalysisResult> analyzeFile(const AnalysisRequest& request) {
        // HTTPè¯·æ±‚åˆ°è¯­è¨€åˆ†ææœåŠ¡
        auto response = httpClient_.post(serviceEndpoint_ + "/analyze", 
                                       request.toJson());
        
        if (response.isSuccess()) {
            return AnalysisResult::fromJson(response.body());
        }
        
        return Result<AnalysisResult>::error("Service unavailable");
    }
};

// ä¸»åˆ†æå™¨é›†æˆ
class MultiLanguageAnalyzer {
private:
    std::unique_ptr<CppAnalyzer> cppAnalyzer_;  // ç°æœ‰C++åˆ†æå™¨
    std::unique_ptr<LanguageAnalysisClient> serviceClient_;
    
public:
    Result<CoverageReport> analyze(const ProjectConfig& config) {
        CoverageReport report;
        
        // å¤„ç†C++æ–‡ä»¶ï¼ˆç°æœ‰é€»è¾‘ä¸å˜ï¼‰
        for (const auto& cppFile : config.getCppFiles()) {
            auto result = cppAnalyzer_->analyze(cppFile);
            report.addCppResult(result);
        }
        
        // å¤„ç†Goæ–‡ä»¶ï¼ˆæ–°å¢é€»è¾‘ï¼‰
        if (config.isGoSupportEnabled()) {
            for (const auto& goFile : config.getGoFiles()) {
                LanguageAnalysisClient::AnalysisRequest request{
                    .language = "go",
                    .filePath = goFile,
                    .config = config.getGoConfig()
                };
                
                auto result = serviceClient_->analyzeFile(request);
                if (result.isSuccess()) {
                    report.addGoResult(result.value());
                }
            }
        }
        
        return Result<CoverageReport>::success(report);
    }
};
```

```cpp
// æœ€å°åŒ–çš„ä»£ç å˜æ›´
class ConfigurableAnalyzer {
private:
    nlohmann::json config_;
    std::unique_ptr<CppAnalyzer> cppAnalyzer_;  // ç°æœ‰åˆ†æå™¨
    
public:
    Result<CoverageReport> analyze(const std::string& projectPath) {
        CoverageReport report;
        
        // C++åˆ†æï¼ˆç°æœ‰é€»è¾‘å®Œå…¨ä¸å˜ï¼‰
        if (config_["languages"]["cpp"]["enabled"]) {
            auto cppResult = analyzeCppFiles(projectPath);
            report.merge(cppResult);
        }
        
        // Goåˆ†æï¼ˆæ–°å¢ï¼Œä½†é€šè¿‡é…ç½®æ§åˆ¶ï¼‰
        if (config_["languages"]["go"]["enabled"]) {
            auto goResult = analyzeGoFiles(projectPath);
            report.merge(goResult);
        }
        
        return Result<CoverageReport>::success(report);
    }
    
private:
    Result<CoverageReport> analyzeGoFiles(const std::string& projectPath) {
        // è°ƒç”¨å¤–éƒ¨Goåˆ†æå™¨
        std::string analyzerPath = config_["languages"]["go"]["analyzer_path"];
        std::string command = analyzerPath + " --project=" + projectPath + 
                             " --config=" + config_.dump();
        
        auto result = executeCommand(command);
        return parseGoAnalysisResult(result);
    }
};
```

```cpp
// å®¹å™¨åŒ–åˆ†æå™¨å®¢æˆ·ç«¯
class ContainerizedAnalyzer {
private:
    std::string containerImage_;
    std::string dockerCommand_;
    
public:
    Result<AnalysisResult> analyze(const std::string& projectPath, 
                                 const nlohmann::json& config) {
        // æ„å»ºDockerå‘½ä»¤
        std::string command = dockerCommand_ + " run --rm " +
                             "-v " + projectPath + ":/workspace " +
                             "-v " + getTempConfigPath(config) + ":/config.json " +
                             containerImage_ + " " +
                             "--workspace=/workspace --config=/config.json";
        
        auto result = executeCommand(command);
        return parseAnalysisResult(result);
    }
};

// ç»Ÿä¸€åˆ†æå™¨æ¥å£
class UnifiedAnalyzer {
private:
    std::unique_ptr<CppAnalyzer> cppAnalyzer_;
    std::unique_ptr<ContainerizedAnalyzer> goAnalyzer_;
    
public:
    Result<CoverageReport> analyze(const ProjectConfig& config) {
        CoverageReport report;
        
        // C++åˆ†æï¼ˆç°æœ‰é€»è¾‘ï¼‰
        auto cppResult = cppAnalyzer_->analyze(config.getCppConfig());
        report.merge(cppResult);
        
        // Goåˆ†æï¼ˆå®¹å™¨åŒ–ï¼‰

            auto goResult = goAnalyzer_->analyze(config.getProjectPath(), 
                                               config.getGoConfig());
            report.merge(goResult);
        }
        
        return Result<CoverageReport>::success(report);
    }
};
```

```cpp
class EnhancedAnalyzer : public ExistingAnalyzer {
private:
    bool goSupportEnabled_;
    std::string goAnalyzerPath_;
    
public:
    // ç°æœ‰C++åˆ†æé€»è¾‘å®Œå…¨ä¸å˜
    Result<CoverageReport> analyze(const ProjectConfig& config) override {
```

```go
// go-analyzer/main.go
package main

import (
    "encoding/json"
    "go/ast"
    "go/parser"
    "go/token"
)

type LogFunction struct {
    File     string `json:"file"`
    Line     int    `json:"line"`
    Column   int    `json:"column"`
    Function string `json:"function"`
    Level    string `json:"level"`
}

func analyzeGoFile(filePath string) ([]LogFunction, error) {
    fset := token.NewFileSet()
    node, err := parser.ParseFile(fset, filePath, nil, parser.ParseComments)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
    
    var logFunctions []LogFunction
    
    ast.Inspect(node, func(n ast.Node) bool {
        if call, ok := n.(*ast.CallExpr); ok {
            if isLogFunction(call) {
                pos := fset.Position(call.Pos())
                logFunctions = append(logFunctions, LogFunction{
                    File:     filePath,
                    Line:     pos.Line,
                    Column:   pos.Column,
                    Function: extractFunctionName(call),
                    Level:    extractLogLevel(call),
                })
            }
        }
        return true
    })
    
    return logFunctions, nil
}
```

#### ç¬¬ä¸‰é˜¶æ®µï¼šé›†æˆä¼˜åŒ–ï¼ˆ1å‘¨ï¼‰
- æ€§èƒ½ä¼˜åŒ–
- é”™è¯¯å¤„ç†å®Œå–„

```cpp
class OptimizedGoAnalyzer {
private:
    std::string goToolPath_;
    bool toolAvailable_;
    
public:
    OptimizedGoAnalyzer() {
        // å¯åŠ¨æ—¶æ£€æŸ¥Goå·¥å…·å¯ç”¨æ€§
        toolAvailable_ = checkGoToolAvailability();
    }
    
    Result<LogCoverageResult> analyze(const ProjectConfig& config) {

            return Result<LogCoverageResult>::error(
                "Go analysis tool not available. Please install go-analyzer.");
        }
        
        // æ‰¹é‡å¤„ç†Goæ–‡ä»¶ï¼Œå‡å°‘è¿›ç¨‹å¯åŠ¨å¼€é”€
        std::vector<std::string> goFiles = config.getGoFiles();
        if (goFiles.empty()) {
            return Result<LogCoverageResult>::success({});
        }
        
        // ä¸€æ¬¡æ€§åˆ†ææ‰€æœ‰Goæ–‡ä»¶
        std::string command = buildAnalysisCommand(goFiles, config);
        auto result = executeCommand(command);
        
        return parseResults(result);
    }
    
private:
    std::string buildAnalysisCommand(const std::vector<std::string>& files,
                                   const ProjectConfig& config) {
        std::ostringstream cmd;
        cmd << goToolPath_ << " --batch";
        
        // ä¼ é€’é…ç½®
        cmd << " --config=" << config.getGoConfigPath();
        
        // ä¼ é€’æ–‡ä»¶åˆ—è¡¨
        for (const auto& file : files) {
            cmd << " " << file;
        }
        
        return cmd.str();
    }
};
```

#### 2.2 Go ASTè§£ææ ¸å¿ƒé€»è¾‘ï¼ˆ3å¤©ï¼‰

**ä¸»è¦æ–‡ä»¶å®ç°**ï¼š

**main.go**ï¼š
```go
package main

import (
    "encoding/json"
    "flag"
    "fmt"
    "os"
    "github.com/dlogcover/go-analyzer/internal/analyzer"
    "github.com/dlogcover/go-analyzer/internal/config"
)

func main() {
    var (
        filePath   = flag.String("file", "", "Go source file to analyze")
        configPath = flag.String("config", "", "Configuration file path")
        outputPath = flag.String("output", "", "Output file path (default: stdout)")
    )
    flag.Parse()

    if *filePath == "" {
        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Error: --file parameter is required\n")
        os.Exit(1)
    }

    // åŠ è½½é…ç½®
    cfg, err := config.LoadConfig(*configPath)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Error loading config: %v\n", err)
        os.Exit(1)
    }

    // åˆ†æGoæ–‡ä»¶
    analyzer := analyzer.New(cfg)
    result, err := analyzer.AnalyzeFile(*filePath)
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Error analyzing file: %v\n", err)
        os.Exit(1)
    }

    // è¾“å‡ºç»“æœ
    jsonData, err := json.MarshalIndent(result, "", "  ")
    if err != nil {
        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Error marshaling result: %v\n", err)
        os.Exit(1)
    }

    if *outputPath != "" {
        err = os.WriteFile(*outputPath, jsonData, 0644)
        if err != nil {
            fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "Error writing output file: %v\n", err)
            os.Exit(1)
        }
    } else {
        fmt.Println(string(jsonData))
    }
}
```

**internal/analyzer/analyzer.go**ï¼š
```go
package analyzer

import (
    "go/ast"
    "go/parser"
    "go/token"
    "path/filepath"
    "github.com/dlogcover/go-analyzer/internal/config"
    "github.com/dlogcover/go-analyzer/internal/types"
)

type Analyzer struct {
    config *config.Config
    fset   *token.FileSet
}

func New(cfg *config.Config) *Analyzer {
    return &Analyzer{
        config: cfg,
        fset:   token.NewFileSet(),
    }
}

func (a *Analyzer) AnalyzeFile(filePath string) (*types.AnalysisResult, error) {
    // è§£æGoæ–‡ä»¶
    node, err := parser.ParseFile(a.fset, filePath, nil, parser.ParseComments)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to parse file: %w", err)
    }

    result := &types.AnalysisResult{
        FilePath:  filePath,
        Language:  "go",
        Functions: []types.FunctionInfo{},
    }

    // éå†ASTæŸ¥æ‰¾å‡½æ•°å’Œæ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
    ast.Inspect(node, func(n ast.Node) bool {
        if funcDecl, ok := n.(*ast.FuncDecl); ok && funcDecl.Name != nil {
            funcInfo := a.analyzeFunctionDecl(funcDecl)
            result.Functions = append(result.Functions, funcInfo)
        }
        return true
    })

    return result, nil
}
```

#### 2.3 æ—¥å¿—å‡½æ•°è¯†åˆ«é€»è¾‘ï¼ˆ3å¤©ï¼‰

**å®ç°è¦ç‚¹**ï¼š
- è¯†åˆ«æ ‡å‡†åº“logåŒ…å‡½æ•°è°ƒç”¨
- è¯†åˆ«Logrusæ—¥å¿—å‡½æ•°è°ƒç”¨
- è¯†åˆ«Zap Loggerå’ŒSugaredLoggerè°ƒç”¨
- æ”¯æŒæ–¹æ³•é“¾è°ƒç”¨ï¼ˆå¦‚`logger.WithField().Info()`ï¼‰
- æå–æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨çš„å‚æ•°ä¿¡æ¯

**internal/analyzer/log_call_analyzer.go**ï¼š
```go
package analyzer

import (
    "go/ast"
    "go/token"
    "strings"
    "github.com/dlogcover/go-analyzer/internal/types"
)

func (a *Analyzer) analyzeCallExpr(callExpr *ast.CallExpr) *types.LogCall {
    funcName := a.getFunctionName(callExpr.Fun)
    if funcName == "" {
        return nil
    }

    // æ£€æŸ¥æ˜¯å¦ä¸ºé…ç½®çš„æ—¥å¿—å‡½æ•°
    if !a.isLogFunction(funcName) {
        return nil
    }

    pos := a.fset.Position(callExpr.Pos())
    
    // æå–å‚æ•°
    args := []string{}
    for _, arg := range callExpr.Args {
        if argStr := a.getArgumentString(arg); argStr != "" {
            args = append(args, argStr)
        }
    }

    return &types.LogCall{
        Function:  funcName,
        Line:      pos.Line,
        Column:    pos.Column,
        Arguments: args,
        Level:     a.getLogLevel(funcName),
    }
}

func (a *Analyzer) isLogFunction(funcName string) bool {
    // æ£€æŸ¥æ ‡å‡†åº“logå‡½æ•°
    if a.config.StandardLog.Enabled {
        for _, fn := range a.config.StandardLog.Functions {
            if funcName == fn {
                return true
            }
        }
    }

    // æ£€æŸ¥Logruså‡½æ•°
    if a.config.Logrus.Enabled {
        for _, fn := range a.config.Logrus.Functions {
            if funcName == fn || strings.HasSuffix(funcName, "."+fn) {
                return true
            }
        }
    }

    // æ£€æŸ¥Zapå‡½æ•°
    if a.config.Zap.Enabled {
        // æ£€æŸ¥Loggerå‡½æ•°
        for _, fn := range a.config.Zap.LoggerFunctions {
            if strings.HasSuffix(funcName, "."+fn) {
                return true
            }
        }
        // æ£€æŸ¥SugaredLoggerå‡½æ•°
        for _, fn := range a.config.Zap.SugaredFunctions {
            if strings.HasSuffix(funcName, "."+fn) {
                return true
            }
        }
    }

    return false
}
```

```diff
- 
+ /**
+  * @file language_detector.cpp
+  * @brief è¯­è¨€æ£€æµ‹å™¨å®ç°
+  * @copyright Copyright (c) 2023 DLogCover Team
+  */
+ 
+ #include <dlogcover/core/language_detector/language_detector.h>
+ #include <dlogcover/utils/log_utils.h>
+ 
+ #include <algorithm>
+ #include <filesystem>
+ 
+ namespace dlogcover {
+ namespace core {
+ namespace language_detector {
+ 
+ // é™æ€æˆå‘˜å˜é‡å®šä¹‰
+ const std::vector<std::string> LanguageDetector::CPP_EXTENSIONS = {
+     ".cpp", ".cxx", ".cc", ".c++", ".C",  // C++æºæ–‡ä»¶
+     ".h", ".hpp", ".hxx", ".h++", ".hh"   // C++å¤´æ–‡ä»¶
+ };
+ 
+ const std::vector<std::string> LanguageDetector::GO_EXTENSIONS = {
+     ".go"  // Goæºæ–‡ä»¶
+ };
+ 
+ SourceLanguage LanguageDetector::detectLanguage(const std::string& filePath) {
+     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("æ£€æµ‹æ–‡ä»¶è¯­è¨€ç±»å‹: %s", filePath.c_str());
+     
+     if (filePath.empty()) {
+         LOG_WARNING("æ–‡ä»¶è·¯å¾„ä¸ºç©ºï¼Œæ— æ³•æ£€æµ‹è¯­è¨€ç±»å‹");
+         return SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN;
+     }
+     
+     // æ£€æŸ¥C++æ–‡ä»¶æ‰©å±•å
+     if (hasCppExtension(filePath)) {
+         LOG_DEBUG_FMT("æ£€æµ‹åˆ°C++æ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+         return SourceLanguage::CPP;
+     }
+     
+     // æ£€æŸ¥Goæ–‡ä»¶æ‰©å±•å
+     if (hasGoExtension(filePath)) {
+         LOG_DEBUG_FMT("æ£€æµ‹åˆ°Goæ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+         return SourceLanguage::GO;
+     }
+     
+     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("æœªçŸ¥æ–‡ä»¶ç±»å‹: %s", filePath.c_str());
+     return SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN;
+ }
+ 
+ bool LanguageDetector::hasCppExtension(const std::string& path) {
+     return hasAnyExtension(path, CPP_EXTENSIONS);
+ }
+ 
+ bool LanguageDetector::hasGoExtension(const std::string& path) {
+     return hasAnyExtension(path, GO_EXTENSIONS);
+ }
+ 
+ std::string LanguageDetector::getLanguageName(SourceLanguage language) {
+     switch (language) {
+         case SourceLanguage::CPP:
+             return "C++";
+         case SourceLanguage::GO:
+             return "Go";
+         case SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN:
+         default:
+             return "Unknown";
+     }
+ }
+ 
+ bool LanguageDetector::hasAnyExtension(const std::string& path, const std::vector<std::string>& extensions) {
+     if (path.empty() || extensions.empty()) {
+         return false;
+     }
+     
+     std::string fileExt = getFileExtension(path);
+     if (fileExt.empty()) {
+         return false;
+     }
+     
+     // åœ¨æ‰©å±•ååˆ—è¡¨ä¸­æŸ¥æ‰¾åŒ¹é…é¡¹
+     return std::find(extensions.begin(), extensions.end(), fileExt) != extensions.end();
+ }
+ 
+ std::string LanguageDetector::getFileExtension(const std::string& path) {
+     try {
+         std::filesystem::path filePath(path);
+         std::string extension = filePath.extension().string();
+         
+         // è½¬æ¢ä¸ºå°å†™ä»¥è¿›è¡Œä¸åŒºåˆ†å¤§å°å†™çš„æ¯”è¾ƒ
+         std::transform(extension.begin(), extension.end(), extension.begin(), ::tolower);
+         
+         return extension;
+     } catch (const std::exception& e) {
+         LOG_WARNING_FMT("è·å–æ–‡ä»¶æ‰©å±•åå¤±è´¥: %s, é”™è¯¯: %s", path.c_str(), e.what());
+         return "";
+     }
+ }
+ 
+ } // namespace language_detector
+ } // namespace core
+ } // namespace dlogcover 
```

```diff
+ ast_analyzer::Result<bool> CppAnalyzerAdapter::analyze(const std::string& filePath) {
+     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("C++åˆ†æå™¨é€‚é…å™¨åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());

+ std::string CppAnalyzerAdapter::getStatistics() const {
+     const auto& results = getResults();
+     size_t totalFunctions = 0;
+     size_t totalLogCalls = 0;
+     
+     for (const auto& nodeInfo : results) {
+         if (nodeInfo) {
+             totalFunctions += nodeInfo->functions.size();
+             for (const auto& func : nodeInfo->functions) {
+                 totalLogCalls += func.logCalls.size();
+             }
+         }
+     }
+     
+     return "C++åˆ†æç»Ÿè®¡: " + std::to_string(results.size()) + " ä¸ªæ–‡ä»¶, " +
+            std::to_string(totalFunctions) + " ä¸ªå‡½æ•°, " +
+            std::to_string(totalLogCalls) + " ä¸ªæ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨";
+ }
```

```diff
+  * @copyright Copyright (c) 2023 DLogCover Team
```

```diff
+ namespace dlogcover {
+ namespace core {
+ namespace analyzer {
+ 
+ GoAnalyzer::GoAnalyzer(const config::Config& config)
+     : config_(config) {
+     LOG_DEBUG("åˆå§‹åŒ–Goåˆ†æå™¨");
+     
+     // æŸ¥æ‰¾Goåˆ†æå™¨å·¥å…·
+     goAnalyzerPath_ = findGoAnalyzerTool();
+     
+     if (config_.go.enabled) {
+         LOG_INFO("Goè¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒå·²å¯ç”¨");
+         if (goAnalyzerPath_.empty()) {
+             LOG_WARNING("æœªæ‰¾åˆ°Goåˆ†æå™¨å·¥å…·ï¼ŒGoè¯­è¨€åˆ†æåŠŸèƒ½å°†å—é™");
+         } else {
+             LOG_INFO_FMT("Goåˆ†æå™¨å·¥å…·è·¯å¾„: %s", goAnalyzerPath_.c_str());
+         }
+     } else {
+         LOG_DEBUG("Goè¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒæœªå¯ç”¨");
+     }
+ }

+ GoAnalyzer::~GoAnalyzer() {
+     LOG_DEBUG("é”€æ¯Goåˆ†æå™¨");
+ }
+ 
+ ast_analyzer::Result<bool> GoAnalyzer::analyze(const std::string& filePath) {
+     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("Goåˆ†æå™¨åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+     
+     // æ£€æŸ¥Goè¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒæ˜¯å¦å¯ç”¨
+     if (!config_.go.enabled) {
+         LOG_DEBUG("Goè¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒæœªå¯ç”¨ï¼Œè·³è¿‡åˆ†æ");
+         return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+     }
+     
+     // æ£€æŸ¥æ–‡ä»¶æ˜¯å¦ä¸ºGoæ–‡ä»¶
+     auto language = language_detector::LanguageDetector::detectLanguage(filePath);
+     if (language != language_detector::SourceLanguage::GO) {
+         LOG_WARNING_FMT("æ–‡ä»¶ä¸æ˜¯Goæ–‡ä»¶ï¼Œè·³è¿‡åˆ†æ: %s", filePath.c_str());
+         return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+     }
+     
+     // æ£€æŸ¥æ–‡ä»¶æ˜¯å¦å­˜åœ¨
+     if (!std::filesystem::exists(filePath)) {
+         LOG_ERROR_FMT("Goæ–‡ä»¶ä¸å­˜åœ¨: %s", filePath.c_str());
+         return ast_analyzer::makeError<bool>(
+             ast_analyzer::ASTAnalyzerError::FILE_NOT_FOUND,
+             "Goæ–‡ä»¶ä¸å­˜åœ¨: " + filePath
+         );
+     }
+     
+     // é˜¶æ®µ1å ä½ç¬¦å®ç°ï¼šè®°å½•æ–‡ä»¶ä½†ä¸è¿›è¡Œå®é™…åˆ†æ
+     LOG_INFO_FMT("æ£€æµ‹åˆ°Goæ–‡ä»¶: %s (é˜¶æ®µ1å ä½ç¬¦ï¼Œå°†åœ¨é˜¶æ®µ2å®ç°å®Œæ•´åˆ†æ)", filePath.c_str());
+     
+     // åˆ›å»ºå ä½ç¬¦ASTèŠ‚ç‚¹ä¿¡æ¯
+     auto nodeInfo = std::make_unique<ast_analyzer::ASTNodeInfo>();
+     nodeInfo->filePath = filePath;
+     nodeInfo->language = "Go";
+     nodeInfo->isValid = true;
+     
+     // æ·»åŠ å ä½ç¬¦å‡½æ•°ä¿¡æ¯
+     ast_analyzer::FunctionInfo placeholderFunc;
+     placeholderFunc.name = "placeholder_function";
+     placeholderFunc.line = 1;
+     placeholderFunc.column = 1;
+     placeholderFunc.isValid = true;
+     
+     // æ·»åŠ å ä½ç¬¦æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
+     ast_analyzer::LogCallInfo placeholderLog;
+     placeholderLog.functionName = "log.Println";
+     placeholderLog.line = 1;
+     placeholderLog.column = 1;
+     placeholderLog.level = "info";
+     placeholderLog.isValid = true;
+     
+     placeholderFunc.logCalls.push_back(placeholderLog);
+     nodeInfo->functions.push_back(placeholderFunc);
+     
+     results_.push_back(std::move(nodeInfo));
+     
+     // æ›´æ–°ç»Ÿè®¡ä¿¡æ¯
+     statistics_.analyzedFiles++;
+     statistics_.totalFunctions++;
+     statistics_.totalLogCalls++;
+     
+     LOG_INFO_FMT("Goæ–‡ä»¶åˆ†æå®Œæˆï¼ˆå ä½ç¬¦ï¼‰: %s", filePath.c_str());
+     return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+ }
```

+ ast_analyzer::Result<bool> MultiLanguageAnalyzer::analyzeFile(const std::string& filePath) {
+     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("å¤šè¯­è¨€åˆ†æå™¨åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+     
+     // æ£€æµ‹æ–‡ä»¶è¯­è¨€ç±»å‹
+     auto language = language_detector::LanguageDetector::detectLanguage(filePath);
+     
+     // æ›´æ–°ç»Ÿè®¡ä¿¡æ¯
+     statistics_.totalFiles++;
+     
+     // æ ¹æ®è¯­è¨€ç±»å‹è·¯ç”±åˆ°ç›¸åº”çš„åˆ†æå™¨
+     switch (language) {
+         case language_detector::SourceLanguage::CPP: {
+             LOG_DEBUG_FMT("è·¯ç”±åˆ°C++åˆ†æå™¨: %s", filePath.c_str());
+             statistics_.cppFiles++;
+             
+             auto it = analyzers_.find(language);
+             if (it != analyzers_.end() && it->second) {
+                 auto result = it->second->analyze(filePath);
+                 updateStatistics(language, !result.hasError());
+                 return result;
+             } else {
+                 LOG_ERROR("C++åˆ†æå™¨æœªåˆå§‹åŒ–");
+                 updateStatistics(language, false);
+                 return ast_analyzer::makeError<bool>(
+                     ast_analyzer::ASTAnalyzerError::INITIALIZATION_FAILED,
+                     "C++åˆ†æå™¨æœªåˆå§‹åŒ–"
+                 );
+             }
+         }
+         
+         case language_detector::SourceLanguage::GO: {
+             LOG_DEBUG_FMT("è·¯ç”±åˆ°Goåˆ†æå™¨: %s", filePath.c_str());
+             statistics_.goFiles++;
+             
+             auto it = analyzers_.find(language);
+             if (it != analyzers_.end() && it->second) {
+                 if (it->second->isEnabled()) {
+                     auto result = it->second->analyze(filePath);
+                     updateStatistics(language, !result.hasError());
+                     return result;
+                 } else {
+                     LOG_DEBUG_FMT("Goè¯­è¨€æ”¯æŒæœªå¯ç”¨ï¼Œè·³è¿‡æ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+                     return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+                 }
+             } else {
+                 LOG_WARNING_FMT("Goåˆ†æå™¨æœªåˆå§‹åŒ–ï¼Œè·³è¿‡æ–‡ä»¶: %s", filePath.c_str());
+                 return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+             }
+         }
+         
+         case language_detector::SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN:
+         default: {
+             LOG_DEBUG_FMT("æœªçŸ¥æ–‡ä»¶ç±»å‹ï¼Œè·³è¿‡åˆ†æ: %s", filePath.c_str());
+             statistics_.unknownFiles++;
+             return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+         }
+     }
+ }

+ ast_analyzer::Result<bool> MultiLanguageAnalyzer::analyzeAll() {
+     LOG_INFO("å¤šè¯­è¨€åˆ†æå™¨å¼€å§‹åˆ†ææ‰€æœ‰æ–‡ä»¶");
+     
+     const auto& sourceFiles = sourceManager_.getSourceFiles();
+     bool hasErrors = false;
+     
+     for (const auto& fileInfo : sourceFiles) {
+         auto result = analyzeFile(fileInfo.path);
+         if (result.hasError()) {
+             LOG_ERROR_FMT("åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: %s, é”™è¯¯: %s", 
+                          fileInfo.path.c_str(), result.errorMessage().c_str());
+             hasErrors = true;
+         }
+     }
+     
+     LOG_INFO_FMT("å¤šè¯­è¨€åˆ†æå™¨å®Œæˆæ‰€æœ‰æ–‡ä»¶åˆ†æï¼Œå…±å¤„ç† %zu ä¸ªæ–‡ä»¶", sourceFiles.size());
+     
+     if (hasErrors) {
+         return ast_analyzer::makeError<bool>(
+             ast_analyzer::ASTAnalyzerError::ANALYSIS_FAILED,
+             "éƒ¨åˆ†æ–‡ä»¶åˆ†æå¤±è´¥"
+         );
+     }
+     
+     return ast_analyzer::makeSuccess(true);
+ }

```diff
+ // æµ‹è¯•Goæ–‡ä»¶æ£€æµ‹
+ TEST_F(LanguageDetectorTest, DetectGoFiles) {

+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("package.go"), SourceLanguage::GO);
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("/path/to/file.go"), SourceLanguage::GO);
+ }

+ // æµ‹è¯•æœªçŸ¥æ–‡ä»¶ç±»å‹
+ TEST_F(LanguageDetectorTest, DetectUnknownFiles) {
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("test.txt"), SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN);

+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("test.java"), SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN);
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("test"), SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN);
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage(""), SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN);

+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("test.Cpp"), SourceLanguage::CPP);
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("test.Go"), SourceLanguage::GO);

+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("./src/main.go"), SourceLanguage::GO);
+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::detectLanguage("../include/header.h"), SourceLanguage::CPP);
+ }

+     EXPECT_TRUE(LanguageDetector::hasCppExtension("test.h"));
+     EXPECT_FALSE(LanguageDetector::hasCppExtension("test.go"));
+     EXPECT_FALSE(LanguageDetector::hasCppExtension("test.txt"));
+ 
+     EXPECT_TRUE(LanguageDetector::hasGoExtension("test.go"));
+     EXPECT_FALSE(LanguageDetector::hasGoExtension("test.cpp"));
+     EXPECT_FALSE(LanguageDetector::hasGoExtension("test.h"));
+ }

+     EXPECT_EQ(LanguageDetector::getLanguageName(SourceLanguage::UNKNOWN), "Unknown");
+ }
```

```diff
+     "log"
+     "fmt"
+     "github.com/sirupsen/logrus"
+     "go.uber.org/zap"
+ )
+ 
+ func testFunction() {
+     fmt.Println("This is a test function")
+     log.Println("Standard log message")
+     
+     // Logrus logging
+     logrus.Info("Logrus info message")
+     logrus.Error("Logrus error message")
+     
+     // Zap logging
+     logger, _ := zap.NewProduction()
+     defer logger.Sync()
+     logger.Info("Zap info message")
+     logger.Error("Zap error message")
+ }
+ 
+ func main() {
+     testFunction()
+ }
```

```diff

+ package main
+ 
+ import (
+ 	"encoding/json"
+ 	"fmt"
+ 	"go/ast"
+ 	"go/parser"
+ 	"go/token"
+ 	"os"
+ 	"path/filepath"
+ 	"strings"
+ )
+ 
+ // AnalysisRequest åˆ†æè¯·æ±‚ç»“æ„
+ type AnalysisRequest struct {
+ 	FilePath string                 `json:"file_path"`
+ 	Config   GoAnalysisConfig       `json:"config"`
+ }
+ 
+ // GoAnalysisConfig Goåˆ†æé…ç½®
+ type GoAnalysisConfig struct {
+ 	StandardLog StandardLogConfig `json:"standard_log"`
+ 	Logrus      LogrusConfig      `json:"logrus"`
+ 	Zap         ZapConfig         `json:"zap"`
+ 	Golib       GolibConfig       `json:"golib"`
+ }
+ 
+ // StandardLogConfig æ ‡å‡†åº“logé…ç½®
+ type StandardLogConfig struct {
+ 	Enabled   bool     `json:"enabled"`
+ 	Functions []string `json:"functions"`
+ }
+ 
+ // LogrusConfig Logrusæ—¥å¿—åº“é…ç½®
+ type LogrusConfig struct {
+ 	Enabled   bool     `json:"enabled"`
+ 	Functions []string `json:"functions"`
+ }
+ 
+ // ZapConfig Zapæ—¥å¿—åº“é…ç½®
+ type ZapConfig struct {
+ 	Enabled           bool     `json:"enabled"`
+ 	LoggerFunctions   []string `json:"logger_functions"`
+ 	SugaredFunctions  []string `json:"sugared_functions"`
+ }
+ 
+ // GolibConfig Golibæ—¥å¿—åº“é…ç½®
+ type GolibConfig struct {
+ 	Enabled   bool     `json:"enabled"`
+ 	Functions []string `json:"functions"`
+ }
+ 
+ // AnalysisResult åˆ†æç»“æœç»“æ„
+ type AnalysisResult struct {
+ 	Success   bool           `json:"success"`
+ 	Error     string         `json:"error,omitempty"`
+ 	FilePath  string         `json:"file_path"`
+ 	Functions []FunctionInfo `json:"functions"`
+ 	LogCalls  []LogCallInfo  `json:"log_calls"`
+ 	Statistics Statistics    `json:"statistics"`
+ }
+ 
+ // FunctionInfo å‡½æ•°ä¿¡æ¯
+ type FunctionInfo struct {
+ 	Name       string        `json:"name"`
+ 	Line       int           `json:"line"`
+ 	Column     int           `json:"column"`
+ 	EndLine    int           `json:"end_line"`
+ 	EndColumn  int           `json:"end_column"`
+ 	HasLogging bool          `json:"has_logging"`
+ 	LogCalls   []LogCallInfo `json:"log_calls"`
+ }
+ 
+ // LogCallInfo æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨ä¿¡æ¯
+ type LogCallInfo struct {
+ 	FunctionName string `json:"function_name"`
+ 	Library      string `json:"library"`
+ 	Level        string `json:"level"`
+ 	Line         int    `json:"line"`
+ 	Column       int    `json:"column"`
+ 	Message      string `json:"message,omitempty"`
+ }
+ 
+ // Statistics ç»Ÿè®¡ä¿¡æ¯
+ type Statistics struct {
+ 	TotalFunctions int `json:"total_functions"`
+ 	TotalLogCalls  int `json:"total_log_calls"`
+ 	LibraryStats   map[string]int `json:"library_stats"`
+ }
+ 
+ // GoAnalyzer Goä»£ç åˆ†æå™¨
+ type GoAnalyzer struct {
+ 	config   GoAnalysisConfig
+ 	fileSet  *token.FileSet
+ 	logFuncs map[string]LogLibrary
+ }
+ 
+ // LogLibrary æ—¥å¿—åº“ä¿¡æ¯
+ type LogLibrary struct {
+ 	Name      string
+ 	Functions map[string]string // function -> level
+ }
+ 
+ // NewGoAnalyzer åˆ›å»ºGoåˆ†æå™¨
+ func NewGoAnalyzer(config GoAnalysisConfig) *GoAnalyzer {
+ 	analyzer := &GoAnalyzer{
+ 		config:   config,
+ 		fileSet:  token.NewFileSet(),
+ 		logFuncs: make(map[string]LogLibrary),
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	analyzer.initializeLogFunctions()
+ 	return analyzer
+ }
+ 
+ // initializeLogFunctions åˆå§‹åŒ–æ—¥å¿—å‡½æ•°æ˜ å°„
+ func (ga *GoAnalyzer) initializeLogFunctions() {
+ 	// æ ‡å‡†åº“log
+ 	if ga.config.StandardLog.Enabled {
+ 		stdLib := LogLibrary{
+ 			Name:      "standard",
+ 			Functions: make(map[string]string),
+ 		}
+ 		for _, fn := range ga.config.StandardLog.Functions {
+ 			level := "info"
+ 			if strings.Contains(strings.ToLower(fn), "fatal") {
+ 				level = "fatal"
+ 			} else if strings.Contains(strings.ToLower(fn), "panic") {
+ 				level = "panic"
+ 			}
+ 			stdLib.Functions["log."+fn] = level
+ 		}
+ 		ga.logFuncs["log"] = stdLib
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// Logrus
+ 	if ga.config.Logrus.Enabled {
+ 		logrusLib := LogLibrary{
+ 			Name:      "logrus",
+ 			Functions: make(map[string]string),
+ 		}
+ 		for _, fn := range ga.config.Logrus.Functions {
+ 			level := strings.ToLower(fn)
+ 			if level == "warning" {
+ 				level = "warn"
+ 			}
+ 			logrusLib.Functions["logrus."+fn] = level
+ 		}
+ 		ga.logFuncs["logrus"] = logrusLib
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// Zap Logger
+ 	if ga.config.Zap.Enabled {
+ 		zapLib := LogLibrary{
+ 			Name:      "zap",
+ 			Functions: make(map[string]string),
+ 		}
+ 		for _, fn := range ga.config.Zap.LoggerFunctions {
+ 			level := strings.ToLower(fn)
+ 			if level == "dpanic" {
+ 				level = "panic"
+ 			}
+ 			zapLib.Functions["logger."+fn] = level
+ 		}
+ 		for _, fn := range ga.config.Zap.SugaredFunctions {
+ 			level := strings.ToLower(strings.TrimSuffix(fn, "f"))
+ 			if level == "dpanic" {
+ 				level = "panic"
+ 			}
+ 			zapLib.Functions["sugar."+fn] = level
+ 		}
+ 		ga.logFuncs["zap"] = zapLib
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// Golib
+ 	if ga.config.Golib.Enabled {
+ 		golibLib := LogLibrary{
+ 			Name:      "golib",
+ 			Functions: make(map[string]string),
+ 		}
+ 		for _, fn := range ga.config.Golib.Functions {
+ 			level := "info" // é»˜è®¤çº§åˆ«
+ 			golibLib.Functions["golib."+fn] = level
+ 		}
+ 		ga.logFuncs["golib"] = golibLib
+ 	}
+ }
+ 
+ // AnalyzeFile åˆ†æGoæ–‡ä»¶
+ func (ga *GoAnalyzer) AnalyzeFile(filePath string) (*AnalysisResult, error) {
+ 	result := &AnalysisResult{
+ 		FilePath:   filePath,
+ 		Functions:  []FunctionInfo{},
+ 		LogCalls:   []LogCallInfo{},
+ 		Statistics: Statistics{
+ 			LibraryStats: make(map[string]int),
+ 		},
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// è§£æGoæ–‡ä»¶
+ 	src, err := os.ReadFile(filePath)
+ 	if err != nil {
+ 		return nil, fmt.Errorf("è¯»å–æ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: %v", err)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	file, err := parser.ParseFile(ga.fileSet, filePath, src, parser.ParseComments)
+ 	if err != nil {
+ 		return nil, fmt.Errorf("è§£æGoæ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: %v", err)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// éå†ASTèŠ‚ç‚¹
+ 	ast.Inspect(file, func(n ast.Node) bool {
+ 		switch node := n.(type) {
+ 		case *ast.FuncDecl:
+ 			if node.Name != nil {
+ 				funcInfo := ga.analyzeFunctionDecl(node)
+ 				result.Functions = append(result.Functions, funcInfo)
+ 				result.LogCalls = append(result.LogCalls, funcInfo.LogCalls...)
+ 			}
+ 		}
+ 		return true
+ 	})
+ 	
+ 	// è®¡ç®—ç»Ÿè®¡ä¿¡æ¯
+ 	result.Statistics.TotalFunctions = len(result.Functions)
+ 	result.Statistics.TotalLogCalls = len(result.LogCalls)
+ 	
+ 	for _, logCall := range result.LogCalls {
+ 		result.Statistics.LibraryStats[logCall.Library]++
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	result.Success = true
+ 	return result, nil
+ }
+ 
+ // analyzeFunctionDecl åˆ†æå‡½æ•°å£°æ˜
+ func (ga *GoAnalyzer) analyzeFunctionDecl(funcDecl *ast.FuncDecl) FunctionInfo {
+ 	pos := ga.fileSet.Position(funcDecl.Pos())
+ 	end := ga.fileSet.Position(funcDecl.End())
+ 	
+ 	funcInfo := FunctionInfo{
+ 		Name:      funcDecl.Name.Name,
+ 		Line:      pos.Line,
+ 		Column:    pos.Column,
+ 		EndLine:   end.Line,
+ 		EndColumn: end.Column,
+ 		LogCalls:  []LogCallInfo{},
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// åˆ†æå‡½æ•°ä½“ä¸­çš„æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
+ 	if funcDecl.Body != nil {
+ 		ast.Inspect(funcDecl.Body, func(n ast.Node) bool {
+ 			if callExpr, ok := n.(*ast.CallExpr); ok {
+ 				if logCall := ga.analyzeCallExpr(callExpr); logCall != nil {
+ 					funcInfo.LogCalls = append(funcInfo.LogCalls, *logCall)
+ 					funcInfo.HasLogging = true
+ 				}
+ 			}
+ 			return true
+ 		})
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	return funcInfo
+ }
+ 
+ // analyzeCallExpr åˆ†æå‡½æ•°è°ƒç”¨è¡¨è¾¾å¼
+ func (ga *GoAnalyzer) analyzeCallExpr(callExpr *ast.CallExpr) *LogCallInfo {
+ 	pos := ga.fileSet.Position(callExpr.Pos())
+ 	
+ 	// è·å–å‡½æ•°è°ƒç”¨åç§°
+ 	funcName := ga.getFunctionName(callExpr.Fun)
+ 	if funcName == "" {
+ 		return nil
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// æ£€æŸ¥æ˜¯å¦ä¸ºæ—¥å¿—å‡½æ•°
+ 	for libName, lib := range ga.logFuncs {
+ 		if level, exists := lib.Functions[funcName]; exists {
+ 			return &LogCallInfo{
+ 				FunctionName: funcName,
+ 				Library:      libName,
+ 				Level:        level,
+ 				Line:         pos.Line,
+ 				Column:       pos.Column,
+ 			}
+ 		}
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	return nil
+ }
+ 
+ // getFunctionName è·å–å‡½æ•°è°ƒç”¨åç§°
+ func (ga *GoAnalyzer) getFunctionName(expr ast.Expr) string {
+ 	switch e := expr.(type) {
+ 	case *ast.Ident:
+ 		return e.Name
+ 	case *ast.SelectorExpr:
+ 		if pkg, ok := e.X.(*ast.Ident); ok {
+ 			return pkg.Name + "." + e.Sel.Name
+ 		}
+ 	}
+ 	return ""
+ }
+ 
+ func main() {
+ 	if len(os.Args) < 2 {
+ 		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "ç”¨æ³•: %s <request.json>\n", os.Args[0])
+ 		os.Exit(1)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	requestFile := os.Args[1]
+ 	
+ 	// è¯»å–è¯·æ±‚æ–‡ä»¶
+ 	requestData, err := os.ReadFile(requestFile)
+ 	if err != nil {
+ 		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "è¯»å–è¯·æ±‚æ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: %v\n", err)
+ 		os.Exit(1)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// è§£æè¯·æ±‚
+ 	var request AnalysisRequest
+ 	if err := json.Unmarshal(requestData, &request); err != nil {
+ 		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "è§£æè¯·æ±‚å¤±è´¥: %v\n", err)
+ 		os.Exit(1)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// åˆ›å»ºåˆ†æå™¨
+ 	analyzer := NewGoAnalyzer(request.Config)
+ 	
+ 	// åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶
+ 	result, err := analyzer.AnalyzeFile(request.FilePath)
+ 	if err != nil {
+ 		result = &AnalysisResult{
+ 			Success:  false,
+ 			Error:    err.Error(),
+ 			FilePath: request.FilePath,
+ 		}
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	// è¾“å‡ºç»“æœ
+ 	resultData, err := json.MarshalIndent(result, "", "  ")
+ 	if err != nil {
+ 		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "åºåˆ—åŒ–ç»“æœå¤±è´¥: %v\n", err)
+ 		os.Exit(1)
+ 	}
+ 	
+ 	fmt.Print(string(resultData))
+ } 
```

```diff
+ #!/usr/bin/env python3
+ """
+ Goåˆ†æå™¨æ¨¡æ‹Ÿå™¨ - ç”¨äºæµ‹è¯•å¤šè¯­è¨€åˆ†æå™¨é›†æˆ
+ """
+ 
+ import json
+ import sys
+ import os
+ import re
+ 
+ def analyze_go_file(file_path):
+     """åˆ†æGoæ–‡ä»¶å¹¶è¿”å›ç»“æœ"""
+     if not os.path.exists(file_path):
+         return {
+             "success": False,
+             "error": f"æ–‡ä»¶ä¸å­˜åœ¨: {file_path}",
+             "file_path": file_path
+         }
+     
+     try:
+         with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:
+             content = f.read()
+     except Exception as e:
+         return {
+             "success": False,
+             "error": f"è¯»å–æ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: {str(e)}",
+             "file_path": file_path
+         }
+     
+     # ç®€å•çš„æ¨¡å¼åŒ¹é…æ¥è¯†åˆ«å‡½æ•°å’Œæ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
+     functions = []
+     
+     # æŸ¥æ‰¾å‡½æ•°å®šä¹‰
+     func_pattern = r'func\s+(\w+)\s*\([^)]*\)\s*[^{]*\{'
+     func_matches = re.finditer(func_pattern, content)
+     
+     for match in func_matches:
+         func_name = match.group(1)
+         start_pos = match.start()
+         
+         # è®¡ç®—è¡Œå·å’Œåˆ—å·
+         lines_before = content[:start_pos].count('\n')
+         line_start = content.rfind('\n', 0, start_pos) + 1
+         column = start_pos - line_start
+         
+         # æŸ¥æ‰¾å‡½æ•°ä½“ä¸­çš„æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
+         log_calls = []
+         
+         # æŸ¥æ‰¾å‡½æ•°ä½“ç»“æŸä½ç½®ï¼ˆç®€åŒ–å¤„ç†ï¼‰
+         brace_count = 0
+         func_end = start_pos
+         for i, char in enumerate(content[start_pos:], start_pos):
+             if char == '{':
+                 brace_count += 1
+             elif char == '}':
+                 brace_count -= 1
+                 if brace_count == 0:
+                     func_end = i
+                     break
+         
+         func_body = content[start_pos:func_end]
+         
+         # æŸ¥æ‰¾æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨
+         log_patterns = [
+             (r'log\.(\w+)\s*\(', 'standard', 'info'),
+             (r'logrus\.(\w+)\s*\(', 'logrus', None),
+             (r'logger\.(\w+)\s*\(', 'zap', None),
+             (r'sugar\.(\w+)\s*\(', 'zap', None),
+         ]
+         
+         for pattern, library, default_level in log_patterns:
+             for log_match in re.finditer(pattern, func_body):
+                 log_func = log_match.group(1)
+                 log_pos = start_pos + log_match.start()
+                 
+                 # è®¡ç®—æ—¥å¿—è°ƒç”¨çš„è¡Œå·å’Œåˆ—å·
+                 log_lines_before = content[:log_pos].count('\n')
+                 log_line_start = content.rfind('\n', 0, log_pos) + 1
+                 log_column = log_pos - log_line_start
+                 
+                 # ç¡®å®šæ—¥å¿—çº§åˆ«
+                 level = default_level or log_func.lower()
+                 if level == 'warning':
+                     level = 'warn'
+                 
+                 log_calls.append({
+                     "function_name": f"{library}.{log_func}",
+                     "library": library,
+                     "level": level,
+                     "line": log_lines_before + 1,
+                     "column": log_column + 1
+                 })
+         
+         functions.append({
+             "name": func_name,
+             "line": lines_before + 1,
+             "column": column + 1,
+             "end_line": lines_before + 1,  # ç®€åŒ–å¤„ç†
+             "end_column": column + len(func_name),
+             "has_logging": len(log_calls) > 0,
+             "log_calls": log_calls
+         })
+     
+     # è®¡ç®—ç»Ÿè®¡ä¿¡æ¯
+     total_log_calls = sum(len(func["log_calls"]) for func in functions)
+     library_stats = {}
+     for func in functions:
+         for log_call in func["log_calls"]:
+             lib = log_call["library"]
+             library_stats[lib] = library_stats.get(lib, 0) + 1
+     
+     return {
+         "success": True,
+         "file_path": file_path,
+         "functions": functions,
+         "log_calls": [log for func in functions for log in func["log_calls"]],
+         "statistics": {
+             "total_functions": len(functions),
+             "total_log_calls": total_log_calls,
+             "library_stats": library_stats
+         }
+     }
+ 
+ def main():
+     if len(sys.argv) != 2:
+         print(f"ç”¨æ³•: {sys.argv[0]} <request.json>", file=sys.stderr)
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     request_file = sys.argv[1]
+     
+     try:
+         with open(request_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:
+             request = json.load(f)
+     except Exception as e:
+         result = {
+             "success": False,
+             "error": f"è¯»å–è¯·æ±‚æ–‡ä»¶å¤±è´¥: {str(e)}",
+             "file_path": ""
+         }
+         print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     file_path = request.get("file_path", "")
+     if not file_path:
+         result = {
+             "success": False,
+             "error": "è¯·æ±‚ä¸­ç¼ºå°‘file_pathå­—æ®µ",
+             "file_path": ""
+         }
+         print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))
+         sys.exit(1)
+     
+     # åˆ†ææ–‡ä»¶
+     result = analyze_go_file(file_path)
+     
+     # è¾“å‡ºç»“æœ
+     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))
+ 
+ if __name__ == "__main__":
+     main() 
```
